//max value of vectorfloat vector;void loop() {  if (IMU.accelerationAvailable()) {    IMU.readAcceleration(x, y, z);  }  vector = sqrt(x * x + y * y + z * z); //vector to sample the board's movement in every direction  if (vector > max_x ) {    max_x = vector ;    times = 0;    Serial.print(max_x);    Serial.println('\\t');  }  if (vector < max_x ) { //inversed pattern detection (aka I'm moving back the board)    times++;    Serial.print(times);    Serial.println('\\t');  }  if (times > 5 &&  max_x > 4) { //sample some value to avoid bouncing    // Send a C note, to change it refer to a MIDI note map table    // like http://www.opensound.com/dmguide/dmmidi.html   // noteOn(0, 48, 64);   // Channel 0, middle C, normal velocity    noteOn(0, 48, 64);   // Channel 0, middle C, normal velocity    MidiUSB.flush();       //noteOff(0, 48, 64);    max_x = 0.0f; //reset max X value  }}

d_question-submitted: #include <PubSubClient.h>const char* ssid = \"YourWiFiSSID\";const char* password = \"YourWiFiPassword\";const char* mqtt_server = \"your_mqtt_broker_address\";const int mqtt_port = 1883;const char* mqtt_topic = \"soil/moisture\";const char* mqtt_client_id = \"NanoESP32_SoilMoisture\";const int soilMoisturePin = A0;  // Analog pin for soil moisture sensorconst int ledPin = 2;  // Built-in LED pin for Nano ESP32unsigned long lastReadTime = 0;const unsigned long readInterval = 60000;  // Read every 60 seconds// Calibration values (adjust these based on your sensor and soil)const int airValue = 620;    // Value when sensor is in dry airconst int waterValue = 310;  // Value when sensor is in waterWiFiClient espClient;PubSubClient client(espClient);void setup() {  Serial.begin(115200);    pinMode(soilMoisturePin, INPUT);  pinMode(ledPin, OUTPUT);  setup_wifi();  client.setServer(mqtt_server, mqtt_port);  Serial.println(\"Soil Moisture Sensor initialized\");}void setup_wifi() {  delay(10);  Serial.println();  Serial.print(\"Connecting to \");  Serial.println(ssid);  WiFi.begin(ssid, password);  while (WiFi.status() != WL_CONNECTED) {    delay(500);    Serial.print(\".\");  }  Serial.println(\"\");  Serial.println(\"WiFi connected\");  Serial.println(\"IP address: \");  Serial.println(WiFi.localIP());}void reconnect() {  while (!client.connected()) {    Serial.print(\"Attempting MQTT connection...\");    if (client.connect(mqtt_client_id)) {      Serial.println(\"connected\");    } else {      Serial.print(\"failed, rc=\");      Serial.print(client.state());      Serial.println(\" try again in 5 seconds\");      delay(5000);    }  }}void loop() {  if (!client.connected()) {    reconnect();  }  client.loop();  unsigned long currentTime = millis();  if (currentTime - lastReadTime >= readInterval) {    digitalWrite(ledPin, HIGH);  // Turn on LED to indicate reading    int moistureValue = readSoilMoisture();    int moisturePercentage = calculateMoisturePercentage(moistureValue);    printMoistureData(moistureValue, moisturePercentage);    publishMoistureData(moisturePercentage);    lastReadTime = currentTime;    digitalWrite(ledPin, LOW);  // Turn off LED after reading  }  // Other non-blocking code can run here}int readSoilMoisture() {  int sum = 0;  for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {    sum += analogRead(soilMoisturePin);    delay(10);  }  return sum / 10;  // Return average of 10 readings}int calculateMoisturePercentage(int value) {  int percentage = map(value, airValue, waterValue, 0, 100);  return constrain(percentage, 0, 100);}void printMoistureData(int rawValue, int percentage) {  Serial.print(\"Soil Moisture: \");  Serial.print(rawValue);  Serial.print(\" (Raw Value) | \");  Serial.print(percentage);  Serial.print(\"% | Status: \");  Serial.println(getMoistureStatus(percentage));}String getMoistureStatus(int percentage) {  if (percentage < 30) return \"Dry\";  else if (percentage < 70) return \"Moist\";  else return \"Wet\";}void publishMoistureData(int moisturePercentage) {  char msg[50];  snprintf(msg, 50, \"{\\\"moisture\\\": %d}\", moisturePercentage);    if (client.publish(mqtt_topic, msg)) {    Serial.println(\"Moisture data published successfully\");  } else {    Serial.println(\"Failed to publish moisture data\");  }}

lv_chart_get_y_array(chart_pdm, pdm_series);  for( idx=0; idx<PDM_NUMBER_SAMPLES; idx++ )  {    pdm_y_points[idx] = (lv_coord_t)*(dataPDM+idx);    }  lv_chart_refresh(chart_pdm); /*Required after
